text: is a railway station in Yukuhashi, Fukuoka Prefecture, Japan. It is on the Tagawa Line, operated by the Heisei Chikuhō Railway. Trains arrive roughly every 30 minutes. On 1 April 2009, a construction company headquartered in nearby Miyako, , acquired naming rights to the station.
